  "instructions": [
    "In a large saucepan, melt the butter over medium heat. ",
    "Add the ground almonds and cook, stirring frequently, until lightly toasted, about 5 minutes. ",
    "Add the granulated sugar, heavy cream, large egg, ground cardamom, salt, and sweet almond extract to the saucepan. ",
    "Whisk the mixture until smooth. ",
    "Bring the mixture to a simmer and cook, whisking constantly, until thickened, about 5 minutes. ",
    "Remove the saucepan from the heat and stir in the vanilla powder. ",
    "Let the pilaf cool slightly before serving. ",
    "If desired, top with whipped cream. ",
    "Serve warm or chilled. ",
    "Cover and refrigerate for up to a week or freeze for up to 3 months. ",
    "Thaw frozen pilaf overnight in the refrigerator and reheat in the microwave or on the stovetop. "
  ],
